properties.description: The name of the person in the group.

goals.question: What is the distribution of group sizes?
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the number of people in each group and if there are any outliers.

goals.question: What is the most common group size?
goals.rationale: This helps to identify the most common group size and if there are any groups with significantly more or less members.

goals.question: Which person is in the most groups?
goals.rationale: This helps to identify the most active person in the dataset and if there are any outliers.

goals.question: What is the distribution of people across groups?
goals.visualization: stacked bar chart of group and person
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the distribution of people across groups and if there are any groups with significantly more or less members.

goals.question: What is the overlap between groups?
goals.visualization: venn diagram of group and person
goals.rationale: This helps to understand if there are any people who are members of multiple groups and if there are any groups that share members.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='group', kde=False)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group sizes?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    venn_data = data.groupby('person')['group'].apply(set).reset_index()
    venn2([set(venn_data[venn_data['group'].apply(lambda x: 1 in x)]['person']), set(venn_data[venn_data['group'].apply(lambda x: 2 in x)]['person'])], set_colors=('#4C72B0', '#55A868'), set_labels=('Group 1', 'Group 2'))
    plt.title('What is the overlap between groups?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
